Backport of the renderable.rs portion of openai/codex#11064 onto rust-v0.125.0.

Stabilises bottom-anchored flex layout: the FlexAllocationMode enum lets
`render`/`cursor_pos` fill the assigned extent (so fixed children stay pinned
even as flex children change size) while `desired_height` keeps content-based
sizing. The companion insert_history.rs cursor-hide tweak from the same PR is
applied via codex.nix's postPatch instead, because GNU patch can't match the
v0.125.0 wrapping-module imports without unacceptable fuzz.

